<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>0.9.28</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: Virtual Libraries: Easily partition your large calibre library into smaller 'virtual' libraries
    - New: Book details panel: Allow copying of links in the book details panel by right clicking on them.
    - New: Kobo driver: Add support for the new Kobo Aura HD and firmware version 2.5.0
	- New: Metadata download: When showing downloaded covers, allow right clicking on a cover to view a full size version.
	- New: Driver for Easy player cyber book e touch and Droid 4
	- New: Edit ToC: Allow the size of the panels in the location view to be adjusted
	- New: When copying to a library by path, make it more efficient to choose between moving and copying
	- New: When checking if a zip/rar file is a comic or contains a single ebook to be auto-extracted, ignore thumbs.db files inside the archive
    - Fixed: EPUB Input: Fix handling of EPUB files that contain images with non-ascii filenames.
    - Fixed: Device driver: Detect Laser EB720 with newer firmware.
    - Fixed: Fix bug in Danish translation causing books with language Ingush being incorrectly translated as Engelsk
    - Fixed: PDF Output: Fix hyperlinks not working when converting an EPUB whose individual files have names with URL unsafe characters.
	- Fixed: Book polishing: Fix inserting cover into an epub with no cover could lead to incorrect guide entry if the opf is not at the root of the epub.
	- Fixed: ZIP Output: Fix links containing backslashes on windows
	- Fixed: Fix polishing of AZW3 files not working on OS X.
	- Fixed: Polishing books: Fix polishing erroring out if the book being polished has no cover
	- Fixed: RTF Input: Add partial support for hyperlinks to web resources.
	- Fixed: Fix book details panel showing incorrect info after deleting books from a connected device
	- New News Source: Voice of America by Krittika Goyal
	- New News Source: Lightspeed Magazine by Jose Pinto
	- New News Source: The Feature by Jose Pinto
    - Improved News Source: NZZ Online
    - Improved News Source: Baltimore Sun
	- Improved News Source: Metro NL
	- Improved News Source: Financial Times
	- Improved News Source: EcoGeek
	- Improved News Source: comics.com
	- Improved News Source: Psychology Today
	- Improved News Source: Science News
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
